# Architecture Rules

- **200-Line File Limit**: No `.tsx` or `.ts` file may exceed 200 lines. Break into smaller modules.
- **Atomic Design**: Structure components in `src/components/ui/` (atoms), `src/components/composed/` (molecules), and `src/components/sections/` (organisms).
- **TypeScript Strictness**: No `any`. Explicitly type all component props. 
- **Barrel Exports**: Every component directory must have an `index.ts` exporting its contents. Import via the directory path.
- **Zero Lint Suppression**: Never use `eslint-disable`, `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-expect-error`, or `// @ts-nocheck`.
- **Reference**: Always follow rules in `CONVENTIONS.md` and use boilerplate from `COMPONENT_TEMPLATE.md`.
